<!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
<section id="faq" class="pp-faq">
    <div class="pp-section-hdr">
        <p class="pp-section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Common questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know before your pet's first stay.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pp-faq-list">
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                What should I bring for my pet's stay?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                Please bring enough food for the full stay, any medications with clear dosage instructions, and a familiar blanket or toy if your pet finds comfort in one. We provide bedding, bowls, and all the love — you just cover the snacks.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                How will I know my pet is doing well?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                We send daily photo updates through your account. If anything comes up that needs your attention, a staff member will contact you directly by phone or email. No news is good news, but we send photos either way.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                What happens if my pet gets sick during their stay?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                We have a vet on call at all times. If your pet shows any signs of illness we will contact you immediately and, with your authorization, arrange veterinary care. We will never delay treatment in a genuine emergency.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                Do you accommodate special diets or medications?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                Absolutely. Please provide all food and medication with written instructions when you drop off. Our staff follow feeding schedules and dosage instructions precisely. If your pet has a complex medical need, reach out before booking so we can make sure we can meet it.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                What is your cancellation policy?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                Cancellations made more than 48 hours before the start of a booking are fully refunded. Cancellations within 48 hours are reviewed on a case-by-case basis. You can submit a cancellation request any time through your account and our team will respond within 24 hours.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pp-faq-item">
            <button class="pp-faq-q" type="button">
                Are dogs and cats kept separately?
                <span class="pp-faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="pp-faq-a">
                Yes. Dogs and cats have completely separate areas of the facility. All pets have their own private space and are never left unsupervised during group interactions. If you have multiple pets of different species, we accommodate all of them.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

